What were the open-door notes? Open-door notes were a policy of the United States government from the early 1940s to the early 1990s that allowed refugees from communist countries to seek asylum in the United States.

As of 2017, what fraction of the population in India used the internet in the past three months? A recent study by the Pew Research Center found that about one-third of the Indian population used the internet in the past three months.

What percent of Indian citizens used the internet in 2017? A report by the Internet and Mobile Association of India (IAMAI) and Kantar IMRB said that in 2017, the internet user base in India grew by 11 percent to 481 million. This means that about 54 percent of Indian citizens used the internet in 2017.
why does an electrical current travel faster through muscle than it does through fat? The electrical current travels faster through muscle because it is a better conductor than fat.
does muscle contain more water than fat? Muscle tissue contains more water than fat tissue.
